  "notes": "Umbrian (3rd–1st c. BCE). Sabellic language of Umbria. Main source: Iguvine Tablets (7 bronze tablets, longest Italic text outside Latin). Distinctive sibilant /ʃ/ and extensive rhotacism. Substrate in central Italian dialects (Rix 2002).",
